Ques. Functions in JavaScript
Ans~~ Functions in JavaScript are reusable blocks of code designed to perform a specific task. They help in structuring programs, improving code reusability, and reducing redundancy.

Declaring Functions in JavaScript
1. Function Declaration – Defined using the function keyword with a name. It supports hoisting, meaning it can be called before its declaration.
2. Function Expression – Assigned to a variable and does not support hoisting.
3. Arrow Function (ES6) – A concise way to write functions using the => syntax.
4. Functions with Parameters and Return Values – Can accept arguments and return computed values.